<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">[Place Holder o' Doom!!! Will crit with 24 hours]</span></p>
<p>Howdy, apologies for this taking so long!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Line&nbsp;by&nbsp;line&nbsp;and&nbsp;general&nbsp;thoughts.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h1><span>Line by Line</span></h1>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is to be kept in a humanoid containment cell with standard necessities.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The standard necessities could be omitted just because it is assumed. Maybe try something like &quot;SCP-XXXX is to be contained in a standard humanoid containment chamber.&quot; (I changed it to chamber, but you could get away with cell.)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>LED spotlights must be around the subject's cell, allowing no shadows in contact with the cell. Any change in SCP-XXXX is to be reported immediately.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Clinical tone: &quot;LED spotlights must surround the cell, ensuring no shadows come in contact with it. Any change in SCP-XXXX is to be reported immediately.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following incident XXXX-A2, SCP-XXXX-1 has been provided with counseling and further educational within Site-17.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This feels unnecessary. You could axe the &quot;<strong>Update:</strong>&quot; line all together.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is the shadow of XXXX-1, a humanoid appearing as a 32 year old male of Caucasian descent. SCP-XXXX-1 self-identifies as Clarence Carter.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Delete the &quot;self&quot; part of &quot;self-identifies&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX has outlines of a mouth, eyes, and entire body which moves whenever active.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;SCP-XXXX has the illuminated outline of a mouth, eyes, and body similar to that of SCP-XXXX-1.&quot; then delete the sentence right after that.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX can communicate with SCP-XXXX-1 but is incapable of communicating with other organisms.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;SCP-XXXX is capable of communication with SCP-XXXX-1 but is unable to communicate with other organisms.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX can detach itself from XXXX-1 to interact with shadows of objects or people.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;SCP-XXXX is able to detach itself from SCP-XXXX-1 to interact with shadows of objects or people.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Interactions with these shadows correspond to movements with the objects casting them.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;Interactions with these shadows correspond to movements with the objects creating them.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX only loses contact with XXXX-1 on rare occasions. The cause of these incidents are unknown. For more information, see Addenda.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What does this mean? He can detach from -1 at any time, so what is the point of these sentences?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Update_Incident_XXXX-A2:</strong>SCP-XXXX-2 is a painting showing a silhouetted humanoid figure standing on a hill. Further information is limited to personnel above level 3 clearance.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Missing a space, should be &quot;<strong>Update_Incident_XXXX-A2:</strong> SCP-XXXX-2 is a painting showing a silhouetted humanoid figure standing on a hill. Further information is limited to personnel above level 3 clearance.&quot; Further more, I don't see why this is important since you just gave that and there is an entire other addendum dedicated to SCP-XXXX-2.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1 was apprehended after breaking into Virginia State Museum. Following its arrest, it became clear that the entities shadow was non-existent.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Could be &quot;Following SCP-XXXX-1's arrest at the Virginia State Museum, it was observed that SCP-XXXX-1 did not have a shadow.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>At this point, embedded foundation agents reported the anomaly and anesticised witnesses as necessary.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Embedded Foundation agents reported the anomaly and removed it.&quot; or &quot;Embedded Foundation agents reported the anomaly and amnesticised witnesses.&quot; Though, I figure most people wouldn't care enough to notice a shadow. I don't remember the last time I noticed a shadow.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1 was interrogated in foundation custody following its discovery. Two hours later, SCP-XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;). The two objects were designated as SCP-XXXX shortly after.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;SCP-XXXX-1 was interrogated in Foundation custody following its discovery. SCP-XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;). The two objects were collectively designated as SCP-XXXX.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following its discovery, SCP-XXXX and SCP-XXXX-1 were sent through a round of testing, which was designed to gauge SCP-XXXX's capabilities.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Ehh, I don't think this is entirely necessary. Just cut it all together.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Interview was an attempt to uncover any origin/information of SCP-XXXX. The questions went without incident and both SCP-XXXX and -1 complied. It should be noted that SCP-XXXX is referred as &quot;Thomas&quot; by SCP-XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;The Interview was an attempt to uncover any information of SCP-XXXX's origin. It should be noted that SCP-XXXX is referred as &quot;Thomas&quot; by SCP-XXXX.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1 seems highly trustful of SCP-XXXX, and did not hesitate in answering accordingly and truthfully. Possible that he’s holding back on details. He made a sudden change of opinion on the topic of whether to be separated from SCP-XXXX in further interviews when SCP-XXXX made an abrupt change of pace. -Dr. Rose</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;SCP-XXXX-1 seems highly trustful of SCP-XXXX, and did not hesitate in answering accordingly. It is possible that he’s holding back on details. He made a sudden change of opinion on the topic of whether to be separated from SCP-XXXX in further interviews when SCP-XXXX made an abrupt change of pace. -Dr. Rose&quot; Though the wording on &quot;He made a sudden change of opinion on&quot; is still worded a little weird.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX, take the wallet and open it's contents. If able, count the contents.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;SCP-XXXX is to take the wallet and open it's contents. If able, count the contents.&quot; All of the instructions should be written this way or similar.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX moves to be across the wall the desk is against with the contents. XXXX's arm goes across the wall to the table, interacting with the wallet's Shadow. Upon interaction, shadow of the wallet went to the wall, as XXXX lifted it up. The psychical wallet hovered in the air, forcing itself to align with the shadow. SCP-XXXX took all contents out and organized them properly back into the wallet, before putting it back down.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>All of the XXXX's need SCP- in front of them.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Item has been taken for further investigation. It is believed this painting has a connection to SCP-XXXX. The item has been labeled SCP-XXXX-2. Efforts to retrieve Agent Wolf in progress.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;The item was taken for further investigation. It is believed this painting has a connection to SCP-XXXX. This item has been designated SCP-XXXX-2. Efforts to retrieve Agent Wolf are in progress.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>After the retrieval of the anomalous painting, it was imperative to question SCP-XXXX for any information on the item, and further investigation into it's past with XXXX-1. XXXX was given a green-screen and chair to manifest on without the presence of XXXX-1. A journal and pen were supplied for XXXX to answer the questions.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;After the retrieval of SCP-XXXX-2, it was imperative to question SCP-XXXX for any information on the item. SCP-XXXX was given a green-screen and chair to manifest on without the presence of SCP-XXXX-1. A journal and pen were supplied for SCP-XXXX to answer the questions.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;We found a painting in the Museum where you were found. Does that sound familiar to you?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;We found a painting in the Museum. Does that sound familiar to you?&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX and XXXX-1 has stopped all communication. Dr. Doxon was tasked with understand what had happened during Audio_Log_XXXX-52.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>We know the first part. Try &quot;Dr. Doxon was tasked with understand what had happened during Audio_Log_XXXX-52.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;XXXX-1. Before we begin tests, do you mind if I you sit down and we have some quick chit-chat?'</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Try &quot;&quot;XXXX-1. Before we begin tests, do you mind if I you sit down and we have some quick chit-chat?&quot;&quot; (With the &quot; instead of ')</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following Interview XXXX-6, SCP-XXXX-1 has been diagnosed with anxiety and clinical depression. Psychiatric evaluation by foundation also concluded that SCP-XXXX-1 has experienced a significantly stunted psychiatric development. Based on these findings, the Intelligence Quotient (IQ) of the subject has been determined as 80, with a mental age of 15.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm not sure why the first part is entirely necessary. I would suggest cutting it all together just having &quot;Psychiatric evaluation by foundation also concluded that SCP-XXXX-1 has experienced a significantly stunted psychiatric development. Based on these findings, the Intelligence Quotient (IQ) of the subject has been determined as 80, with a mental age of 15.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The note at the end.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Could be done as</p>
<div class="code">
<pre>
<code>&gt; Clarence,
&gt; 
&gt; I didn't mean to hurt you. I didn't mean to lie to you. I only wished to keep you safe. You were the first thing I saw in this world. You were the only thing that kept me going. It's true, that I used you to get back home. But I just wanted to teach you how to live before I left. I knew you couldn't survive without me, so I tried my hardest to teach you everything I knew. This world is cold, dark, and unforgiving. You were my shadow and I was yours. I found my way back home.
&gt; 
&gt; But…
&gt; 
&gt; I didn't know what would happen to you if I left.
&gt; 
&gt; You could have disappeared the moment I went back.
&gt; 
&gt; So I stayed.
&gt; 
&gt; I let myself get caught.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Just to make sure you were okay.
&gt; 
&gt; Please forgive me.
&gt; 
&gt; Your friend, Thomas</code>
</pre></div>
<p>I would also be weary that this can fall to the &quot;Note at the end&quot; trope.</p>
<hr />
<h1><span>Minor Nitpick</span></h1>
<p>I dislike when people add dates and black box some of the numbers. Its not a big deal if you do, I am just particular. Honestly, its up to you to keep them or not.</p>
<hr />
<h1><span>Final Notes</span></h1>
<p>Take out &quot;+ SCP-XXXX Experiments&quot; It doesn't do much other than fill space. I noticed that you have an issue with &quot;SCP-XXXX's&quot; more so the &quot;SCP-&quot; part. You're missing it in almost every instance of XXXX.</p>
<p>Hmm, alright. I think this is alright. Aside from a few issues I pointed out above. I think this could go far. I am worried about the emotional hits coming off a little weird though. We don't entirely have much reason to care for SCP-XXXX and SCP-XXXX-1. Other than that, good job.</p>
<p>Good luck!</p>
<p>I suggest taking this to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5336470&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608776044" alt="cybersqyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5336470)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;">cybersqyd</a></span> or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4916887); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4916887&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608776044" alt="MalyceGraves" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4916887)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4916887); return false;">MalyceGraves</a></span> for more critique.</p>
</div>
