			<div class="content" id="post-content-4851807">
									

<p>I have not got anything on the main site, but here are my thoughts anyway - take these with a grain of salt. If you don't like a proposed change, feel free to ignore it.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;Line&nbsp;by&nbsp;Line&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><br />
<em>Things I would remove will be <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">crossed out</span> and Things I would add will be <span style="text-decoration: underline;">underlined</span>, and things that could be decided by you [E.g specifics] are in [Square brackets]</em></p>
<h4><span>Description</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is the shadow of XXXX-1, Clarence Carter</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would change to</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is the shadow of XXXX-1, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">a humanoid appearing as a [middle-aged] male of [indeterminent] descent. SCP-XXXX-1 self-identifies as</span> Clarence Carter.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX is a sapient shadow with the outlines of a mouth, eyes, and entire body which moves whenever active.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would change to</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-</span>XXXX <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">is a sapient shadow with the</span> has outlines of a mouth, eyes, and entire body which moves whenever active. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">The eyes and mouth appear as illuminated regions within the shadow.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This fixes some clinical tone issues, and makes the appearance clearer, I think.</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX has no way of talking to people outside of XXXX-1</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is not clinical. I would change it to</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-XXXX can communicate with SCP-XXXX-1 but is incapable of communicating with other organisms.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>Stretching itself, XXXX is able to change into different forms.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Again, Clinical tone is off here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-XXXX is relatively amorphous, stretching and morphing into various forms at will.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX can detach itself from XXXX-1 to interact with shadows of objects or people.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As well as changing XXXX and XXXX-1 to SCP-XXXX and SCP-XXXX-1 respectively, I would add the following for clarity.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX can detach itself from XXXX-1 to interact with shadows of objects or people. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Interactions with these shadows correspond to movements with the objects casting them.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>Subject has only left XXXX-1 on rare occasions. Reasons are unknown. More information under Addendum XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Should be changed to something like:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Subject</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-XXXX</span> <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">has</span> only <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">left</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">loses contact with</span> SCP-XXXX-1 on rare occasions. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Reasons are unknown</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">The cause of these incidents are unknown</span>. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">More information under Addendum XXXX.</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">For more information, see Addenda.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<h4><span>Discovery</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX's discovery was on December 3ed, 20██ in Charleston, West Virginia. XXXX-1's apprehension by authorities after breaking into the West Virginia State Museum made It clear that his shadow was nonexistent. Put into the police database, the Foundation took subject from custody for investigation. Two hours later, (after interrogation with XXXX-1) XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;), with both subjects receiving their numbers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Has some SPAG errors and poor phrasing, which I would recommend changing to this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">SCP-XXXX's discovery was</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-XXXX was discovered</span> on December 3<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">e</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">r</span>d, 20██ in Charleston, West Virginia. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">XXXX-1's apprehension by authorities after breaking into the West Virginia State Museum made It clear that his shadow was nonexistent</span>. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">SCP-XXXX-1 was apprehended after breaking into Virginia State Museum. Following its arrest, it became clear that the entities shadow was non-existent. At this point, embedded foundation agents reported the anomaly and anesticised witnesses as necessary.</span> <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Put into the police database, the Foundation took the subject from custody for investigation.</span> _SCP-XXXX-1 was interrogated in foundation custody following its discovery. Two hours later, SCP-XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;). The two objects were designated as SCP-XXXX shortly after.__<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">(after interrogation with XXXX-1) XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;), with both subjects receiving their numbers</span></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h4><span>Addendum XXXX.1</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>XXXX and XXXX-1 go through testing everyday at Six PM, testing the capabilities of XXXX's limitations. XXXX-1 frequently asks XXXX for advice and is a translator for tests. All investigation on XXXX-1's Family has come back with no results.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This phrasing unclear, and the sentence structure is a bit muddled. I would maybe change this to:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Following its discovery, SCP-XXXX and SCP-XXXX-1 were sent through a round of testing, which was designed to gauge SCP-XXXX's capabilities. On-site personnel have noted that SCP-XXXX-1 and SCP-XXXX regularly communicate, with SCP-XXXX-1 asking SCP-XXXX for personal advice, including discussions of SCP-XXXX-1's containment, and apparent amnesia. It should also be noted that investigation into the family or prior life of SCP-XXXX has been inconclusive.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This version establishes -1's 'amnesia' earlier, while also flowing a bit nicer (this is coming from a biased opinion though).</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Foreword:</strong> The Interview was an attempt to uncover any origin/information of SCP-XXXX. The questions went without incident and both SCP-XXXX and -1 complied.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It should probably be noted here that -1 refers to XXXX as 'Thomas' as it introduces minor-confusion later on.</p>
<p>In terms of the interview in itself, I'll give my thoughts on the style in the 'Overall' section, but since I am horrible at writing dialogue, I'll just point out any typos I spotted.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>&lt;The desk would suddenly break apart, one of the limbs giving way. Review of the footage showed XXXX caused this for unknown reasons. Dr. Rose calls maintenance to replace the desk. The interview continued shortly after&gt;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't see why this line's here. This doesn't really add much to the story, as far as I can tell. If you need to keep it in though, change it to:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>&lt;<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">The desk would suddenly break apart, one of the limbs giving way.</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">The desk breaks apart suddenly, with one leg collapsing.</span> Review of the footage <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">showed XXXX caused this for unknown reasons.</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">show that SCP-XXXX caused this by interacting with the shadow of the desk. SCP-XXXX's motivations for this are unknown.</span> Dr. Rose calls maintenance to replace the desk. The interview <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">continued</span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">continues</span> shortly after&gt;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>No, the police to me first.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>You mean 'The police took me first'?</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>No luck. We’ve traveled half of America with no luck.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Maybe</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;No luck. We travelled across half of America, still nothing&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX: &quot;I’m sorry, what? Am I being separated from Thomas?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Do you mean SCP-XXXX-1?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX: &quot;Are you saying that I’m not being compliant now?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Same here.</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;Thomas appears to say something, Clarence looking over.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Shouldn't this be 'SCP-XXXX' for thomas, and 'SCP-XXXX-1' for Clarence? Also, Interview transcripts are in the present tense, so it should be 'SCP-XXXX-1 looks over'.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;Thomas appears to speak over Clarence, Clarence going silent.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Same applies here.</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Expermiment Logs</span></h4>
<p>I'm just gonna say it here, but the experiment logs seem to be kind of&#8230; useless? It kind of seems like a sudden, random shift from the main narrative rather than something useful. I would just specify some bits about how the anomaly works (like seeing in 2D) in the description.</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Update XXXX</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>After further investigation in the State Museum where SCP-XXXX was found, Agent Hart found Agent Wolf had disappeared while examining a painting on exhibit. Item has been taken for further investigation. Most certainly has a connection to SCP-XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would describe the painting here. Also, maybe change 'Most certainly' to 'It is believed this painting has a connection to SCP-XXXX</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Interview XXXX.4</span></h4>
<p>The same thing applies as with the interview above.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;Subject gives a smile&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Maybe just &quot;SCP-XXXX smiles.&quot;</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;XXXX swiftly wrote two giant letters on the second page, taking the whole paper up&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would change to</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;SCP-XXXX writes two large letters on the second page, covering the paper.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;XXXX appears grief stricken&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is unclinical. Maybe say</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;SCP-XXXX appears distressed&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h4><span>Interview XXXX-6</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>I DON'T HAVE A FAMILY, I DON'T HAVE AMNESIA, AND THOMAS IS JUST A FUCKING LIAR!&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't know if a transcription would emphasise text in upper case to show shouting, but that's just me.</p>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>Dr. Doxon: &quot;…&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Should change to</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;Dr. Doxon remains silent.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<p>Closing Statement: SCP-XXXX-1 has gone into forms of irritation and depression. Upon going through a psych eval, it was concluded that XXXX-1's IQ is 80, and while being in the body of a man in his early 30s, he has the mental intelligence of a teenager.</p>
<p>Could be changed to</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following Interview XXXX-6, SCP-XXXX-1 has been diagnosed with anxiety and clinical depression. Psychiatric evaluation by foundation also concluded that SCP-XXXX-1 has experienced a significantly stunted psychiatric development. Based on these findings, the Intelligence Quotient (IQ) of the subject has been determined as 80, with a mental age of 15.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Or something of the like.</p>
<h4><span>Final Update</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<h3><span>+ XXXX's Message</span></h3>
</blockquote>
<p>Maybe should be</p>
<blockquote>
<h3><span>+ Open File</span></h3>
</blockquote>
<p>The inside of the message is fine as far as I can tell.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;Overall&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Overall, this article is a bit meh&#8230; The emotional core of the article doesn't really hit for me, as I just don't feel invested in these two characters. I would replace the experiment logs with a bit of communication between the anomaly, in order to show their personalities when together.</p>
<p>The Article also lacks a hook, with a pretty stock standard opening. This is by no means bad, but It could be improved by adding an update to the containment procedures saying &quot;Following incident XXXX.1 (the discovery of the painting), SCP-XXXX-1 has been provided with counselling and further educational within [Site-102]<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-307376-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-307376-1')">1</a></sup>.&quot; This addition serves to give the reader a hint of what to expect from the article. I would also add the painting discovered as SCP-XXXX-2, describing it nebulously as 'SCP-XXXX-2 is a painting showing a silhouetted humanoid figure standing on a hill. Further information is limited to personnel above level 3 clearance.' Then maybe add a 'LEVEL 3 CLEARANCE REQUIRED - INPUT CREDENTIALS' over the discovery of SCP-XXXX-2. This hooks the reader without spoiling the mystery.</p>
<p>Other stuff I noted, the interviews dialogue feels a bit&#8230; weird? -1 doesn't really have an established personality, and XXXX itself is&#8230; so bad at lying its silly. Furthermore; the speech just doesn't strike me as &#8230; realistic? I don't know how to describe it, but it seems just weirdly worded. If the researchers noted this, it could add more to the idea that SCP-XXXX-1 was created from nothing, but to me it feels unitentional. Karablue may be able to suggest proper changes to the interviews.</p>
<p>With a few changes however, I think this could be really good. I'd recommend reading some other emotional articles to see what works, and revising the story to flow better. But again, this doesn't strike me as a 'first author series one-clone', rather having actual substance behind it. Good luck if you managed to get through this wall of text!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>P.S: Once you have revised the article, feel free to PM me again, and I'll check it over again. Good luck with getting this on the site.</em></p>
