<p>You have definitely made some improvements, but there are still some issues here and there.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&gt;&nbsp;Line&nbsp;by&nbsp;line&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2><span>Special Containment Procedures</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Update:</strong> Following incident XXXX-A2, SCP-XXXX-1 has been provided with counseling and further educational within Site-17.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would list the date the update occurred here and fix some spelling, and phrasing:<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-979426-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-979426-1')">1</a></sup></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Update:</strong> Following incident XXXX-A2, SCP-XXXX-1 has been provided with weekly counselling and a high-school education within Site-17.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2><span>Description</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>Update_Incident_XXXX-A2:SCP-XXXX-2 is a painting showing a silhouetted humanoid figure standing on a hill. Further information is limited to personnel above level 3 clearance.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Space needed between XXXX-A2: and SCP-XXXX-2. I also don't see the point of the lines between the words there. It could just be 'Update Incident XXXX-A2.</p>
<hr />
<h2><span>Discovery</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>3ed</p>
</blockquote>
<p>should be</p>
<blockquote>
<p>3rd</p>
</blockquote>
<h2><span>Addendum XXXX.</span></h2>
<p>Mabye this should be called <strong>Addendum XXXX.1</strong>? It seems to make more sense to me.</p>
<h4><span>Interview XXXX.1</span></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>It should be noted that SCP-XXXX is referred as &quot;Thomas&quot; by SCP-XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Would be phrased better as</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It should be noted that SCP-XXXX-1 reffers to SCP-XXXX by the name &quot;Thomas&quot;.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p><strong>SCP-XXXX-1:</strong> &quot;I knew he was in the Museum. I broke him inside in the first place.&quot;</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rose:</strong> &quot;And what influenced you to break into the Museum?&quot;</p>
<p><strong>SCP-XXXX-1:</strong> &quot;I was scared Thomas was stuck inside, he hadn’t come out in hours.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This seems weird to me. Dr Rose asks why he broke him inside in the first place, then -1 answers that he was already in there? Because Dr Rose doesn't bring him up on the discrepancy, I'd assume this wasn't intentional.</p>
<hr />
<h2><span>+ 'LEVEL 3 CLEARANCE REQUIRED - INPUT CREDENTIALS'</span></h2>
<p>This should follow all of the following text (except for the navigator), as a government document wouldn't just redact one thing that can be discovered anyway with context clues. Also it probably shouldn't have the inverted commas around it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&gt;&nbsp;Overall&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>While a lot of the spelling has been cleaned up, I think the article still suffers from some of the broader issues I pointed out earlier. For one, I think the article could benefit from an Image of either SCP-XXXX-1 or SCP-XXXX in order to break up the text.</p>
<p>I still think the experiment logs detract from the story and are kind of unnecessary. As I said before; this would be more interesting to me if we saw some more characterisation of SCP-XXXX-1 and SCP-XXXX, which could be used in place of the experimentation. Again, this is all my opinion, and I have not got any writing on the site, so take it with a grain of salt.</p>
<p>I think the most important thing this article is in need of is more characterisation because at this point the ending note just doesn't hit for me.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Feel free to PM me again if you make any changes to the article.</em></p>
