<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><em>Gonna note that I can miss stuff; flag things which are right as being wrong and indeed flag things which are deliberately wrong.</em><br />
<em>I'll likely use <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">strikethrough</span> to indicate stuff to remove and <span style="color: green">green text</span> to indicate stuff to add.</em></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following incident XXXX-A2, SCP-XXXX-1 has been provided with counseling and further education within Site-17.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd probably move the 'within Site-17' earlier into the ConProcs; perhaps right after noting it's kept in a humanoid containment chamber.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is the shadow of <span style="color: green">SCP-</span>XXXX-1, a humanoid appearing as a 36-year-old male of Caucasian descent.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Caucasian descent means 'descended from someone from the Caucasus region'; I think you want e.g. 'white American male' here say instead.</p>
<p>I'm also a little iffy about introducing two SCP designations in the first 6 words of your SCP: it feels like perhaps introducing the shadow first and then later the human it's attached to would read better but?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1 identifies as Clarence Carter.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'identifies' here implies 'this is a fake name'; I'd use 'is known as' say</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX has the illuminated outline of a mouth, eyes, and body similar to that of SCP-XXXX-1.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'similar to that' here implies -1 has an illuminated outline of these features too, I'd suggest a semi-colon before similar and perhaps 'similar in appearance' say?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is able to detach itself from SCP-XXXX-1 to interact with shadows of objects or people.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like 'interact with other shadows' would be clearer here; and wouldn't have the weird implication that it can't interact with e.g. animals and plants</p>
<blockquote>
<p>For more information, see Addenda.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd cut this; if you're not specifying a specific place that covers this, it's not necessary. Even if you are, it feels&#8230;odd? Like just trust a reader to assume you'll show this, y'know?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX was discovered on December 3rd, 20██</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Why does knowing the exact date this was discovered on pose a security risk? IMO: unredact this date, and later dates, so we have a concrete idea of the timeline that this is taking place over; as opposed to the current possibility of the discovery being up to 98 years before the rest.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Following SCP-XXXX-1's arrest at the Virginia State Museum, it was observed that SCP-XXXX-1 did not have a shadow.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like it'd be a good idea to hint at why -1 was arrested here; y'know, use the crime to characterise what they're like.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Embedded Foundation agents reported the anomaly and removed it, amnesticised witnesses.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'the anomaly' is singular which implies they only removed one of SCP-XXXX and SCP-XXXX-1; and I'd be clear about which it is here.</p>
<p>The 'amnesticised witnesses' is too 'fragmentary'; it really needs a few more words e.g. 'before they amnesticised witnesses' say.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX was contained by MTF Iota-10 (&quot;Damn Feds&quot;). The two objects were collectively designated as SCP-XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Not really a fan of the vague 'oh yeah a MTF just, contained the shadow' here; and also the two objects were not collectively designated as SCP-XXXX.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It should be noted that SCP-XXXX is referred as &quot;Thomas&quot; by SCP-XXXX<span style="color: green">-1</span>.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><em>&lt;SCP-XXXX observes SCP-XXXX-2</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>-2 is defined ~750 words after this. This doesn't flow right as a result because we have no idea what's happening. Even just using 'observes a painting' with a 'later designated SCP-XXXX-2' footnote would be better.</p>
<p>you're also missing the closing &gt; here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Possible that he’s holding back on details.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd add an 'It's' at the start here; this feels weirdly note like</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He made a sudden change of opinion on the topic of whether to be separated from SCP-XXXX in further interviews when SCP-XXXX made an abrupt change of pace.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is written here like it's summarising something that happened within the interview but it's not so it feels really weird? Like if it was summarising something, it'd be unnecessary cos we'd read it; but instead it appears to be info that Rose has just plucked out of the air.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>LEVEL 3 CLEARANCE REQUIRED - INPUT CREDENTIALS</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This feels altogether too short a note to be in a collapsible.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Agent Hart found Agent Wolf had disappeared while examining a painting on exhibit.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'on exhibit' feels weird to me; maybe 'in the exhibition' or 'on display' would be clearer?</p>
<p>Something about this construction is weird; it kinda implies Hart walked in, saw Wolf had disappeared and then just like, pointed at a random painting and said 'this did it'. It'd work better if there was more of a concrete link between this painting and the one referred to earlier but it feels like Hart should actually like&#8230;see this happening?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Efforts to retrieve Agent Wolf are in progress.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'underway' would be better than 'in progress' here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>After the retrieval of the anomalous painting</p>
</blockquote>
<p>you've given it a designation by now, use the designation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>// &lt;XXXX interacts</p>
</blockquote>
<p>the space between // and &lt; has broken your italics here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>//How about this. I'll answer anything you need to know, and you answer a few of my questions in return.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>missing the closing // here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>idea. And the thought of that alone terrifies me.<br />
// &lt;XXXX</p>
</blockquote>
<p>space issue again; also missing an empty line between these</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Look, giving you answers will only lead to more questions. Questions you wish to have answers to. Some questions shouldn't be answered, Doctor.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>you've got a big chunk of this interview repeating here a few times; it's very weird and I think accidental?</p>
</div>
